The original Wax is a Swift library providing on-device AI agent memory
with hybrid BM25 + HNSW retrieval, MiniLM embeddings on Apple Metal,
single-file .wax storage with WAL crash safety, and token budget management.
Designed for iOS 17+ / macOS 14+.

Wick is a full C++ rewrite and extension of the Wax core, targeting
cross-platform use with Unreal Engine 5 code intelligence. The following
is a summary of changes relative to the original project:

Language and platform:
  - Complete port from Swift to C++20; no Apple platform dependency.
  - Cross-platform build via CMake (Windows, Linux).
  - Storage format changed from .wax to .mv2s (append-only binary with
    WAL ring buffer).

Search and storage:
  - BM25 replaced with SQLite FTS5 full-text search backend.
  - HNSW vector engine reimplemented on top of USearch.
  - MiniLM Apple Metal embeddings replaced with arbitrary GGUF models
    via llama.cpp (platform-independent).

New: HTTP RAG server:
  - Standalone JSON-RPC HTTP server (Poco-based) on port 8080.
  - RPC methods: remember, recall, answer.generate, index.start/status/stop,
    fact.search, blueprint.read/write.

New: MCP bridge for IDE integration:
  - Node.js MCP bridge (stdio) connecting VS Code / Claude Code to the
    RAG server with tools: wax_recall, wax_remember, wax_fact_search,
    wax_blueprint_read, wax_blueprint_write.

New: Unreal Engine 5 code intelligence:
  - UE5 filesystem scanner with .h/.hpp/.cpp/.inl/.inc and .bpl_json support.
  - Regex enricher for UCLASS/USTRUCT/UENUM macros, UPROPERTY/UFUNCTION
    declarations, and class hierarchies.
  - LLM fact enricher via local Qwen2.5-Coder-32B (llama.cpp) extracting
    entity-attribute-value triples from code and Blueprint chunks.
  - Structured EAV triple store with transactional staging.
  - Blueprint round-trip API: read, write, import with automatic backups.

New: Local LLM integration:
  - llama.cpp generation client for RAG-augmented code answers (Qwen3-Coder).
  - llama.cpp embedding provider for optional vector search channel.

New: Background indexing:
  - Async index job manager with states (idle/running/stopped/failed),
    persistent checkpointing, incremental re-indexing via content hashes,
    and resume support.

New: Operational tooling:
  - mv2s_analyzer: binary store inspector.
  - mv2s_vacuum: store compaction tool.
  - PowerShell/batch control panel for server operations.
